<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-22-0681 </DOCNO><TEXT>Expenditures of an intangible nature relating to the exploration for anddevelopment of oil and gas properties fall within the categories of geologicaland geophysical costs (GandG) and intangible drilling and developmentcosts (IDCs). Both types of costs are capital in nature. GandG costsmay be deducted when no oil and gas property is discovered as a resultof the GandG activity or as the property which is discovered is depletedor when it is abandoned. IDCs generally may be deducted when paid orincurred.</TEXT></DOC>